repository-code: >-
  https://github.com/acquire-framework/acquire-framework.github.io
url: https://acquire-framework.github.io
abstract: >-
  ACQUIRE — Acquisition Criteria for Quality, Uncertainty, Integrity,
  Reproducibility, and Evidence — treats the whole acquisition chain of an
  in-the-wild sensing study as a measuring system, and evaluates it along three
  axes: measurement validity, record integrity and provenance, and
  observation-process validity. This artifact bundles the failure taxonomy, the
  reporting checklist, reporting and provenance templates, a reviewer form, and
  a worked example of cross-device synchronization uncertainty.
keywords:
  - reproducibility
  - in-the-wild sensing
  - mobile health
  - wearable computing
  - measurement uncertainty
  - data provenance
  - observation process
  - offline-first architecture
